snippet.textDisplay: From Ustaad Ghulam Ali's ghazal's to Abid Parveen's sufi music, from Ustaad Nusrat Fateh Ali khan's magic to Rahata Fateh Ali's charming voice, from Junaid Jamshed's Dil Dil Pakistan to Alamghir Mili Nagme, from Ali Zafar's Channo to Strings, and lately Coke Studio, loved every bit of Pakistani music being a 80s kid. So many hardships and no support from the government, Pakistani music and musicians never gave up and kept the industry alive. Hit like or comment if you feel proud as a Pakistani or Pakistani music admirer!
